---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-17';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Pricing — Wyreup"
  description="Free tools stay free. PRO is pay-as-you-go credits — no subscription, never expires."
>
  <article class="legal">
    <header>
      <h1>Pricing</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <h2>Free tier</h2>
    <p>
      Every Wyreup tool that can reasonably run in your browser is free,
      forever. No account required. No tracking. No upload. Includes:
      compression, format conversion, PDF editing, image editing, audio
      utilities, code/data helpers, and dozens more.
    </p>

    <h2>PRO tier — credits</h2>
    <p>
      Credits fund the tools that genuinely need a GPU we can't put in
      your browser tab: large-model transcription, summarization,
      translation, background removal at scale, and image upscaling.
    </p>

    <h3>Credit packs</h3>
    <div class="packs">
      <div class="pack">
        <div class="pack__credits">50</div>
        <div class="pack__label">credits</div>
        <div class="pack__price">$4.99</div>
        <div class="pack__per">$0.10 / credit</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pack pack--featured">
        <div class="pack__tag">Best value</div>
        <div class="pack__credits">150</div>
        <div class="pack__label">credits</div>
        <div class="pack__price">$9.99</div>
        <div class="pack__per">$0.067 / credit</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pack">
        <div class="pack__credits">400</div>
        <div class="pack__label">credits</div>
        <div class="pack__price">$19.99</div>
        <div class="pack__per">$0.050 / credit</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>What a credit gets you</h3>
    <table class="cost-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Credits / run</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Transcribe (large model)</td><td>5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Background remove (high-res)</td><td>4</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Upscale 2× (large model)</td><td>4</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Summarize (LLM)</td><td>3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Translate (LLM)</td><td>3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Redact PII (LLM)</td><td>3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sentiment (LLM)</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Named-entity recognition (LLM)</td><td>2</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>How credits work</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>One-time purchase.</strong> No subscription. Buy when you need them.</li>
      <li><strong>Never expire.</strong> Credits stay in your account forever.</li>
      <li><strong>Failed runs are auto-refunded.</strong> If a hosted model errors out, your credits come back to your balance automatically. See the <a href="/legal/refund">refund policy</a> for details.</li>
      <li><strong>Use anywhere.</strong> Browser, CLI, and MCP all draw from the same balance with the same API key.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Payment</h2>
    <p>
      Credit purchases are handled by
      <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lemon Squeezy</a>
      as our merchant of record. They handle VAT, sales tax, receipts,
      and refunds. We never see or store your card number.
    </p>

    <h2>Refunds</h2>
    <p>
      See our <a href="/legal/refund">refund policy</a>. The short version:
      unused credits refundable within 30 days, failed runs auto-refunded.
    </p>

    <h2>What about Wyreup itself?</h2>
    <p>
      The code is open source under the MIT license. You can self-host
      <code>@wyreup/core</code> and run the free tools entirely on your
      own machines, with no relationship to us. The PRO tier exists only
      because hosted GPU inference has a real per-call cost.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4) var(--space-12);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl, 28px);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal ul {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1px 4px;
  }
  .meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .packs {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .packs {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
  .pack {
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-3);
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pack--featured {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .pack__tag {
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--text-on-accent, #000);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .pack__credits {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .pack__label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .pack__price {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .pack__per {
    margin-top: 2px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-subtle);
  }

  .cost-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .cost-table th,
  .cost-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }
  .cost-table th {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .cost-table td {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .cost-table td:last-child {
    text-align: right;
    color: var(--accent-text);
  }
</style>
